<p>October 1915</p>
<p>Tuesday 19</p>
<p>a.m. fatigues.</p>
<p>Artillery duel in morning.</p>
<p>Had first narrow escape.  Sitting in dug out after breakfast when a thud on loose earth startled me, sending a shower of earth down.</p>
<p>Turned out to be a shell cap.</p>
<p>A foot to the right &amp; I should not be writing this.</p>
